Package curam.util.resources

This package contains various utility classes.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    EnvironmentConstants
    Generated EnvironmentConstants environment file.
    EnvironmentConstants.ActionMenus
    These settings enable a system administrator to configure action menus (tab, page, list) to have visibly surfaceable menu items outside of the overflow menu icon.
    EnvironmentConstants.BatchLauncher
    These settings configure the behavior of Curam when problems occur invoking batch programs.
    EnvironmentConstants.CTM
    These settings configure the properties which relate to configuration transport manager.
    EnvironmentConstants.Custom
    These settings allow a developer to replace elements of the Curam infrastructure with their own customized handlers.
    EnvironmentConstants.Database
    These settings configure Curam for database communication.
    EnvironmentConstants.Environment
    These settings configure the environment for your Curam application.
    EnvironmentConstants.IEG
    These settings configure the properties which relate to the IEG Environment.
    EnvironmentConstants.JMX
    These settings configure the JMX infrastructure for your Curam application.
    EnvironmentConstants.KeyServer
    These settings allow a customer to configure the behavior of the KeyServer.
    EnvironmentConstants.Rules
    These settings configure the rules infrastructure of Curam.
    EnvironmentConstants.Security
    These settings configure the authentication behavior of Curam.
    EnvironmentConstants.SessionManagement
    Contains all the configurations for the Session Management.
    EnvironmentConstants.SMTP
    These settings configure the environment in which the SMTP client element of Curam operates.
    EnvironmentConstants.Test
    These settings configure those elements of Curam which are useful for Unit Testing.
    EnvironmentConstants.Trace
    These control what diagnostic information (in addition to errors which are always logged) is written to the application server's diagnostics file.
    EnvironmentConstants.Workflow
    These settings configure the properties which relate to the Workflow Environment.
    EnvironmentConstants.XMLServer
    These settings configure the environment in which the XML Server will be used.
    Trace.CuramMethodInvocationHandler
    CuramMethodInvocationHandler is an interface that must be implemented by all method trace handlers.
    XMLParserCache.DBFactory
    Document builder factory.
    XMLParserCache.SPFactory
    SAX parser factory.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    BidiEngine
    Implementation of the Bidi engine.
    ByteArrayUtil
    This class provides various convenience methods for byte array manipulation.
    Configuration
    Gets application runtime properties.
    DatabaseShortname
    Utility class to handle shortening of database related metadata to the its required length.
    DBtoJMS
    Provides an API to initiate the database-to-JMS message transfer process.
    DBtoJMSHttpClient
    The client part of a HTTP interaction between the batch launcher and application server.
    GeneralConstants
    This class provides a grouping of constants that are used in multiple places in the infrastructure code.
    KeySet
    The names of the commonly used key sets.
    Locale
    Provides convenience fields and methods for accessing various locale-sensitive formatting facilities in Java.
    MeasureTime
    Utility class for measuring and displaying elapsed time.
    MessageAppender
    Custom log4j2 appender to use primarily in Tests.
    ProgramLocale
    This class contains a number of utility methods relating to Locales.
    SimpleHttpClientUtils
    Some utilities for manually sending and receiving HTTP requests and responses.
    SimpleHttpClientUtils.HeaderEntry
    Represents a HTML request header entry.
    SMTPConnection
    Provides interfaces for communicating with an SMTP (simple mail transfer protocol) mail server.
    StringUtil
    StringUtil provides various convenience methods for string manipulation that are not provided by the JDK.
    StructCompare
    StructCompare is provided as a means of comparing Curam generated structures.
    Trace
    Manages debug tracing in the Curam server.
    Trace.CuramMethodInvocationHandlerDefault
    CuramMethodInvocationHandlerDefault is the default method trace handler for Curam.
    TraceLogger
    This class extends the Log4 Logger without providing any extra functionality.
    UniqueIDUtil
    Utility class to handle UniqueID manipulation for the zOS database platform.
    XMLParserCache
    A thread local cache for XML parsers that are relatively expensive to instantiate.
    XMLParserCache.DBFactoryDefault
    Default implementation of a document builder factory.
    XMLParserCache.SPFactoryDefault
    Default implementation of a SAX factory.
    XMLParserConstants
    A class containing common configuration constants for XML parsers.

Package curam.util.resources Description

This package contains various utility classes.
